{"id":5406,"date":"2012-08-20T12:44:07","date_gmt":"2012-08-20T16:44:07","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=5406"},"modified":"2021-12-05T10:57:07","modified_gmt":"2021-12-05T06:57:07","slug":"resurrection-prophet-hawd-wudu","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/20\/resurrection-prophet-hawd-wudu\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hawd: The Prophet recognizes believers at the Fountain"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Verily, my fountain is wider than the distance between Aylah and &#8216;Adan. Its water is whiter than ice, sweeter than honey and milk. Its cups are more numerous than the stars. Verily, I will block some people from it, just as a man blocks camels from his fountain.<\/strong>\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, will you recognize us on that Day?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Yes, you will have marks which no one among people will have but you. You will come to me with a blazing forehead and bright hands and feet from the traces of ablution<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 247<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<strong> \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u062d\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0636\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0652\u0639\u064e\u062f\u064f \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0629\u0